Within the next decade, some 77 million people in the United States will enter
retirement age, and many of them are expected to offer their skills and
experience to work as volunteers.   Better health, longer life-spans and a
desire to give something back to society are among the reasons motivating many
to volunteer.  Producer Zulima Palacio has this report narrated by Deborah
Block on what is being called a "new army of volunteers".
 
 
 
 
